Definitions & Software Scope
For the purposes of this agreement, "The Software" refers to the AVR & C Containerized Build Factory and all of its internal components, scripts, and architectures. This explicitly includes, but is not limited to:
- The Client-Side Deployment Architecture: Scripts responsible for packaging local firmware source code (e.g., CompilingYourProject.sh, CompilingYourProject.ps1) and configuration generators.
- The Server-Side Build Engine (ContainerApp): The isolated Docker container environment, including the Flask application logic (app.py), the Nginx reverse proxy configurations (nginx.conf), container orchestration scripts (DockerRelated.sh), and the unified compilation pipelines for standard C, AVR-GCC, and Unity unit testing.

